The paper proposes a novel unsupervised domain adaptation framework based on deep neural networks with batch normalization layers. The paper focuses on adapting to different domains in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper mainly deals with deep learning models and convolutional neural networks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
